b'WISEST at a Glance'
b'A UIC faculty program that started in 2003 in the Office of the Vice Provost for Faculty Affairs, in collaboration with the Center of Research in Women and Gender, WISEST\xe2\x80\x99s main goal is to increase the number, participation and leadership of minority and majority women in academic science and engineering, through institutional transformations.'
b'Between 2006-2012, WISEST was supported by an NSF ADVANCE Grant (totalling USD 3.3 million) and was guided by the Vice Provost for Faculty Affairs, the Vice Chancellor for Research, the Dean of \xc2\xa0the College of Engineering (COE) and the Dean of College of Liberal Arts and Sciences (LAS), alongside an ample team of UIC faculty, staff and students. Since 2012, WISEST has continued its many activities, receiving generous support and guidance from the Vice Provost for Faculty Affairs, the Provost, the COE Dean and the LAS Dean.'
b'WISEST\xe2\x80\x99s key programs include:'
b'WISEST is represented by Faculty Facilitators from the following 11 STEM departments from COE and LAS:'
b'Richard and Loan Hill Department of\xc2\xa0Bioengineering'
b' Chemical Engineering'
b' Civil and Materials Engineering'
b'Computer Science'
b'Electrical and Computer Engineering'
b'Mechanical and Industrial Engineering'
b'Biological Sciences'
b'Chemistry'
b'Earth and Environmental Sciences'
b'Mathematics, Statistics and Computer Science'
b'Physics'
